subSection.paragraph:
Stenodynerus de Saussure, 1863
is a genus of small-sized potter wasps, comprising 168 species and 26 subspecies distributed in all global regions except for sub-Saharan Africa and Australia .Of these, 45 species and 11 subspecies are recorded from the Palearctic region (Carpenter, unpublished). Most Palearctic species were revised by Gusenleitner (1981) , but the subsequent description of several new species, taxonomic changes, and new records from the region make that revision outdated ( Castro & Sanza 2009 ;
Fateryga et al. 2020
; Giordani Soika 1986 ; Gusenleitner 1985 , 1999 , 2001b , 2004 , 2008 , 2012 ; Kim 1999 ;
Ma et al. 2016
;
Qasim et al. 2018
). In his 1981 revision, Gusenleitner divided the Palearctic species into five informal species-groups, and characterized the
fastidiosissimus
-group as follows: “ Mit Ausnahme je einer Färbungform und Subspecies haben die Arten Binden auf den Tergiten I-V (♀), bzw. I-VI (♂), die Augenausrandung ist nie gelb gezeichnet, das 2. Tergit ist vor dem Endrand im seitlichen Profil flach. Der Clypeus des Männchens ist gleichmässig flach konvex ” (= “With the exception of one color form and one subspecies each, the species have bands on tergites I-V (♀), or I-VI (♂), the eye margin is never marked yellow, the second tergite is flat in front of the apical edge in lateral view. Male clypeus is uniformly weakly convex”). It is to be noted that the black eye margin is not a constant character, as males always have a yellow line on the lower half of inner eye margin and, though rare, some females may present hints of a yellow line.

OLML
—Oberösterreichisches Landesmuseum, Linz; 
Austria
;

Total DNA was extracted from one leg (
Villalta et al. 2021
), dissected from the investigated individuals. Each dissected leg was placed in 2 mL microtubes filled with 1 mL of the specific digestion buffer (
Cilia et al. 2022
) and incubated for 36 hours at 56 °C. The specific digestion buffer consisted of 5 mM CaCl2, 2% sodium dodecyl sulphate (SDS), 65 mM dithiothreitol (DTT), 450 μg/ml proteinase K, 150 mM Tris buffer pH 8 and 100 mM NaCl (
Cilia et al. 2022
). The total DNA purification was performed using a phenol-chloroform extraction (UltrapureTM Phenol: Chloroform: Isoamyl Alcohol, ThermoFisher Scientific, Waltham, MA, USA ) (
Cilia et al. 2022
). The obtained DNA was quantified using the spectrophotometer Infinite 200 PRO NanoQuantTM (TECAN Life Technologies, Männedorf, Switzerland ) and stored at -20 °C until the analysis. As negative control, double-distilled Rnase-Dnasefree water was used for all of these processes.

Amplification of mithocondrial DNA (mtDNA) was performed using primer pairs able to amplify a 710 bp fragment within the highly conserved region coding for the Cytochrome C oxidase subunit I (COI) gene: LCO1490 (5’-GGTCAACAAATCATAAAGATATTGG-3’) and HC02198 (5’-TAAACTTCAGGGTGACCAAAAAATCA-3’) (
Folmer et al. 1994
).

